---

### âœ… **A gentle focus watch loop**

```js
const focusWatcher = setInterval(() => {
  const active = document.activeElement;
  console.log('[Focus Watcher]', active);
}, 250); // Adjust interval if needed
```

âœ… This logs `document.activeElement` every 250 ms â€” so youâ€™ll see exactly *when* and *who* grabs focus as you drag, click buttons, or let the slider rest.  
âœ… If you spot the culprit, you can clear it:  
